SLIDE 1: TITLE SLIDE
- Project Name: Florish - Floral E-Commerce Website
- Subtitle: BCA Final Year Academic Capstone Project
- Student Name / Roll Numbers: [Student Credentials]
- Guide Name: [Project Advisor Name]

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLIDE 2: PROJECT ABSTRACT & INTRODUCTION
- Overview: Decoupled Web application selling hand-arranged seasonal bouquets.
- Motivation: Modernize local florist businesses through dynamic online catalogs.
- Objective: Provide smooth shopping, wishlist, cart caching, and admin inventory controls.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLIDE 3: PROBLEM STATEMENT & PROPOSED SYSTEM
- Problem: Manual brick-and-mortar ordering lacks home delivery tracking, persistent shopping lists, and remote catalogs.
- Proposed System: Dynamic 3-tier architecture (Static HTML/CSS, Node/Express REST APIs, MongoDB cloud/local cluster) with JWT and Multer file upload.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLIDE 4: SYSTEM TECH STACK
- Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 Variables, responsive media breakpoints, dynamic modular JS.
- Backend: Node.js, Express.js middleware server.
- Database: MongoDB Mongoose collections models.
- Image Upload: Multer disk storage config.
- Security: Crypt password (Bcrypt), REST Session sign (JWT).

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLIDE 5: SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE
- Decoupled client-server requests flow.
- Static components dynamically load shared navbar/footers.
- Backend routing mounts controllers, models validation, and global error catches.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLIDE 6: ENTITY RELATIONAL (ER) MODEL
- Collections list: Users, Products, Carts, Orders, Wishlists, Reviews.
- Cardinality links maps. Compound uniqueness indexes for reviews.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLIDE 7: KEY FEATURES AND USER INTERFACES
- Client Area: Catalog search, Price sliders, cart badge updates.
- Auth: JWT token headers interceptor inside client fetch api calls.
- Backoffice: metrics grids counters, stock quantity additions, track updates.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
SLIDE 8: TESTING & CONCLUSION
- Authentication sessions test validation profiles.
- Automated tests verifying DB cast and Multer file type catches.
- Future Scope: Live WhatsApp messaging notifications, online credit card Stripe gateways.
========================================================================
